<br>
I plan to do the following, create a character in each Realm on 3 different Servers.  I will post the character names and server names here.  I intend on purchasing this game the day it comes out.  If we all chose realms on the right servers we can all play together.  Blood Circle will live on as guilds play an active roll in DAoC.  I cannot wait for this game.  3 reasons:  No camping. The weapons and armor made or found in this game decay with wear and time.  At times, quests are given for armor and weapons that do not decay, but each quest is different for each player.  A quest book is kept as a log so that you never forget where you are at. 2) You do not choose your &quot;final&quot; class until you've ding'd 20.  This allow's you to choose what you &quot;think&quot; you want to be at the start, but after you've been in your skin for awhile. You add your advance class and become virtually a totally different player.  This seperation, I feel, would elimenate a lot of the PC casting that we have in EQ.  3) The PvP.  The reason why you have to choose a Realm per server is awesome.  Imagine an on-line world where your greatest enemy isn't an Orc, of a Frenzied Ghoul, but an Elf from Hybernia with a raiding party into a village you are protecting?  There is no inter-realm dialogue.  If you want to speak to the &quot;enemy&quot; you would be face-to-face, probably in combat. You are not able to loot the individual, however, as you defend your realm or attack another, you gain Realm points that serve as a counter for Glory.  As you rise in Glory so does your reputation, quests, etc.  Inter-Realm play is designed primarily for those players 20 and above (Advanced Players) and Team play is a must.  Imagine if you will a &quot;hunting party&quot; of Blood Circle heading into &quot;enemy&quot; territory.  Rumor had it that a similiar expedition was to take place on the other side.  The two coalitions meet in the &quot;no man's land&quot; and a huge battle occurs.  We rally our forces and they rally theirs...nothing, and I mean nothing can match that.  When DAoC comes out, I will establish BC's Servers, our name will live on....in Camelot.<br>
<br>
In Service to the Dream,<br>
<br>
Soulshiver Coeurdeglace<br>
